HEADWORD: Eclaircissement
<hw>E*clair"cisse*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
fr. <ets>⟦eacute⟧claircir</ets>. See <er>Eclaircise</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <def>The clearing up of anything which is obscure or not
easily understood; an explanation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>eclaircissement</qex> ended in the discovery of the
informer.</q> <rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

